		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>This page provides information on how to use Air Manager 5.x.<br />
</p>
<h1><span id="Download_.26_Install"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Download_&amp;_Install">Download &amp; Install</span></h1>
<p>Information on how to download &amp; install Air Manager can be found <a href="/index.php?title=Air_Manager_5.x_Installation" title="Air Manager 5.x Installation">here</a>
</p>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Flight_simulator_plugins">Flight simulator plugins</span></h1>
<p>In order to connect Air Manager to your flight simulator, you have to install our flight simulator plugin(s).<br />
Information on how to install the flight simulator plugins can be found <a href="/index.php?title=Flight_Simulator_Plugins_Installation" title="Flight Simulator Plugins Installation"> here</a>.
</p>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="General_usage">General usage</span></h1>
<p>If you are new to Air Manager, we recommend watching this video first:
<br />
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/McYTeIB9qT4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
<br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Adding_a_new_instrument_panel">Adding a new instrument panel</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Add_panel.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/2/2c/AM5_Add_panel.jpg/300px-AM5_Add_panel.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="251" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/2/2c/AM5_Add_panel.jpg/450px-AM5_Add_panel.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/2c/AM5_Add_panel.jpg/600px-AM5_Add_panel.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Add_panel.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Adding a new panel</div></div></div>
<ul><li>You can add a new panels by clicking on the '+' sign next to the 'Panels' in the left menu. Or you can do the same by clicking the 'Add panel' button on the top right corner of the Air Manager window.</li>
<li>A new window will appear, with a selection of premade panels you can choose from. It is possible to filter on aircraft, by either selection one on the aircraft list on the left, or filtering by entering a piece of text on the top.</li>
<li>Select your panel of choice, and double click on the panel, or click the 'Add' button on the bottom.</li>
<li>After you have selected the panel of choice, you get to select a layout. Some panels have multiple layouts, for multiple display formats, or common panel configurations. (with or without GPS). Air Manager will normally put a panel full screen on a selected monitor. It is also possible to make your own window with custom dimensions.</li></ul>
<p><br />
</p>
<div style="background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1); border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Warning.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/18px-Warning.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/27px-Warning.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/36px-Warning.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">Some of the panels are premium panels, which means you have to buy them first for them to become available. A 'buy' button will be visible for premium panels that haven't been bought yet.</span></div>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Changing_instruments_within_an_existing_instrument_panel">Changing instruments within an existing instrument panel</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Home.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/7/77/AM5_Home.jpg/300px-AM5_Home.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="266" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/7/77/AM5_Home.jpg/450px-AM5_Home.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/77/AM5_Home.jpg/600px-AM5_Home.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Home.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Panel selected, revealing its details on the right</div></div></div>
<ul><li>Start by choosing the panel you wish to edit, by clicking on it on the left menu. Once highlighted, details about the selected panel are shown on the right.</li>
<li>In the <b>layout section</b>, you can move, resize, add or remove instruments.
<ul><li><b>Add</b> an instrument by pressing the '+ Add instrument' button on the top right of the layout section.</li>
<li><b>Remove</b> an instrument by clicking on the instrument with the right mouse button, and select 'Remove'.</li>
<li><b>Move</b> an instrument by dragging the instrument around (same as you would do in windows)</li>
<li><b>Resize</b> an instrument by grabbing one of the corner squares, and dragging it.</li></ul></li></ul>
<p><br />
</p>
<div style="background: lightyellow; border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Lightbulb.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/18px-Lightbulb.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="22" srcset="/images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/27px-Lightbulb.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/36px-Lightbulb.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">Air Manager normally snaps instruments together, to help align them. Press the 'ctrl' button while dragging to disable snapping</span></div>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Changing_the_position_and_location_of_an_instrument_panel">Changing the position and location of an instrument panel</span></h2>
<ul><li>Start by choosing the panel you wish to edit, by clicking on it on the left menu. Once highlighted, details about the selected panel are shown on the right.</li>
<li>The <b>Window preferences section</b> lets you configure where the panel should be positioned, and should behave.
<ul><li>The <b>resize window</b> button lets you resize the panel, giving you the option to scale the instruments within to the new dimensions.</li>
<li><b>Input mode</b> lets you select if the panel is accepting mouse, touch or both inputs.</li>
<li>When <b>Locked</b> is active, it will prevent the panel from accidentally moving.</li>
<li><b>Always on top</b> will make this panel show up above other windows.</li>
<li><b>Focusable</b> makes the window grab focus (or not) in the OS.</li>
<li>Enabling the <b>Click-through</b> option makes mouse input go through the panel to windows below. This is essential when you want a pop out window from the flight simulator behind the Air Manager panel.</li></ul></li></ul>
<p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Adding_devices">Adding devices</span></h2>
<p>Air Manager supports a wide array of devices. The sections below will explain more on how to get them connected, and how to use them.
</p><p><br />
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Knobster">Knobster</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Knobster.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/f/fe/Device_Knobster.jpg/300px-Device_Knobster.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="396" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/f/fe/Device_Knobster.jpg/450px-Device_Knobster.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fe/Device_Knobster.jpg/600px-Device_Knobster.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Knobster.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>The knobster</div></div></div>
<ul><li>Air Manager will automatically connect your your <b>Knobster</b> when it is connected to your PC.</li>
<li>The Knobster will show up in the Device list</li>
<li>Select the panel you wish to use the knobster with, scroll down through its settings, and select your Knobster from the list.</li></ul>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="DIY_knobster">DIY knobster</span></h4>
<p>It is possible to create your own knobster. More information on how to do that can be found <a href="/index.php?title=Knobster_DIY" title="Knobster DIY"> here</a>.
</p>
<ul><li><b>Adding a DIY knobster</b> device to Air Manager can be done by pressing the '+' sign next to 'Devices' on the left menu, or pressing the '+ Add device' button on the top right of Air Manager.</li>
<li>Select the DIY Knobster options, and proceed.</li>
<li>Select the COM port the device is connect to, and proceed. Make sure to enable the 'flash option'</li>
<li>The device will show up in the Device list</li>
<li>Select the panel you wish to use the knobster with, scroll down through its settings, and select your DIY knobster from the list.</li></ul>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="RealSimGear">RealSimGear</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_RealSimGear.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/3/3e/Device_RealSimGear.jpg/300px-Device_RealSimGear.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="225" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/3/3e/Device_RealSimGear.jpg/450px-Device_RealSimGear.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3e/Device_RealSimGear.jpg/600px-Device_RealSimGear.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_RealSimGear.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>RealSimGear device</div></div></div>
<p>Air Manager supports multiple RealSimGear devices:
</p>
<div style="column-count:2">
<ul><li>GMA350</li>
<li>GFC500</li>
<li>GFC700</li>
<li>G1000XFD</li>
<li>GCU47X</li>
<li>GCU479</li>
<li>GNS430</li>
<li>GNS530</li></ul>
</div>
<p><br />
</p>
<ul><li><b>Adding a RealSimGear</b> device to Air Manager can be done by pressing the '+' sign next to 'Devices' on the left menu, or pressing the '+ Add device' button on the top right of Air Manager.</li>
<li>Select the RealSimGear options, and proceed.</li>
<li>Select the COM port the device is connect to, and proceed.</li>
<li>The device will show up in the Device list</li>
<li>Select the added RealSimGear device in the list, and configure a plugin</li>
<li>The plugin handles the connection between the device and the simulator. Select the plugin that most closely matches your aircraft.</li></ul>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Flight_Illusion">Flight Illusion</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:261px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Flight_Illusion_Interface_Board.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/0/02/Device_Flight_Illusion_Interface_Board.jpg" decoding="async" width="259" height="194" class="thumbimage" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Flight_Illusion_Interface_Board.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Flight Illusion interface board</div></div></div>
<ul><li>Adding a Flight Illusion <b>Interface board</b>, <b>Engine Cluster</b> or <b>I/O board</b> to Air Manager can be done by pressing the '+' sign next to 'Devices' on the left menu, or pressing the '+ Add device' button on the top right of Air Manager.</li>
<li>Select the device you with to add, and proceed.</li>
<li>Select the COM port the device is connect to, and other optional settings, and proceed.</li>
<li>The device will show up in the Device list</li>
<li>Select the device in the list, and configure a plugin</li>
<li>The plugin handles the connection between the device and the simulator. Select the plugin that most closely matches your aircraft.</li></ul>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Octavi_IFR-1">Octavi IFR-1</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/7/73/Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp/300px-Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp.png" decoding="async" width="300" height="225" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/7/73/Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp/450px-Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/73/Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp/600px-Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Device_Octavi_IFR-1.webp" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Octavi IFR-1</div></div></div>
<ul><li>The IFR-1 device is plug &amp; play, and should automatically show up in the device list</li>
<li>Select the device in the list, and configure a plugin</li>
<li>The plugin handles the connection between the Octavi IFR-1 and the simulator. Select the plugin that most closely matches your aircraft.</li></ul>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Adding_hardware_components">Adding hardware components</span></h2>
<p>Air Manager has support for the following hardware components:
</p>
<div style="column-count:2">
<ul><li>Digital inputs and outputs</li>
<li>Analogue inputs and outputs</li>
<li>LEDs</li>
<li>Buttons</li>
<li>Switches</li>
<li>Rotary encoders</li>
<li>PWM outputs</li>
<li>Character displays</li>
<li>Button arrays</li>
<li>Stepper motors</li></ul>
</div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Preparing_your_board">Preparing your board</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Preparing_board.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/1/18/AM5_Preparing_board.jpg/300px-AM5_Preparing_board.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="271" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/1/18/AM5_Preparing_board.jpg/450px-AM5_Preparing_board.jpg 1.5x, /images/1/18/AM5_Preparing_board.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Preparing_board.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Selecting COM port and flash settings for an Arduino Micro</div></div></div>
<p>Before we can start using your board or choice, we have to prepare it. Air Manager will load the necessary software in the board.
</p>
<ul><li>To <b>add your board</b>, click on the '+' sign next to 'Devices' in the menu on the left, or click the '+ Add device' button on the top right.</li>
<li>Select the <b>Raspberry Pi Pico</b>, <b>Arduino</b> or <b>Flight Illusion I/O board</b> option. These can be used to connect hardware components.</li>
<li>Follow on-screen instructions. Make sure to enable the <b>Flash</b> option when possible.</li>
<li><b>Channel</b> is used to make a distinction between multiple board of the same type.</li>
<li>Your board should appear in the <b>Devices list</b> on the left side of Air Manager.</li></ul>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Mapping_physical_pins_to_the_simulator">Mapping physical pins to the simulator</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/a/a1/AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg/300px-AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="249" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/a/a1/AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg/450px-AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a1/AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg/600px-AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Mapping_pins.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Mapping pins of the 'Clock / OAT' hardware function</div></div></div>
<ul><li>Once the board is operational, we can start assigning pins to events in the sim</li>
<li>Select the panel to which you wish to add hardware capabilities. Note that it will only be operational when that panel is active/showing.</li>
<li>Add hardware by clicking the <b>Add hardware</b> button on the right side.</li>
<li>Select what simulator function you wish to couple to your hardware</li>
<li>A list of hardware components will show up. Configure which pins should be used for each component.</li></ul>
<p><br />
</p>
<div style="background: lightyellow; border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Lightbulb.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/18px-Lightbulb.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="22" srcset="/images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/27px-Lightbulb.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6f/Lightbulb.png/36px-Lightbulb.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">If a hardware function is missing, you can always create your own. Just a bit of programming knowledge is required. More information can be found <a href="/index.php?title=I/O_Connection_examples" title="I/O Connection examples"> here</a>.</span></div>
<p><br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Manage_connection_between_Air_Manager_and_your_flight_simulator">Manage connection between Air Manager and your flight simulator</span></h2>
<p>By default, Air Manager automatically connects to you simulator, when both are on the same network (same router).
</p><p>It is possible to disable this automatic connection, and select your own IP address or host name of the computer which is running your flight simulator. This setting can be found in the Settings section within Air Manager.
<br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Managing_licenses">Managing licenses</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Account.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/5/57/AM5_Account.jpg/300px-AM5_Account.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="403" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/5/57/AM5_Account.jpg/450px-AM5_Account.jpg 1.5x, /images/5/57/AM5_Account.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Account.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Account window</div></div></div>
<p>Your license is connected to the hardware ID of your computer. You are entitled to 3 resets per license. The number of resets per license is limited because our software uses an offline licensing system. This means that, after the license has been activated, the computer does not have to be connected to the internet to verify the license. Therefore there has to be a limit. If you happen to run into the limit of 3 resets, then please send in a <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.siminnovations.com/support-tickets">support ticket</a>.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Reset_a_license">Reset a license</span></h3>
<p>You can reset the license yourself:
</p>
<ul><li>Open Air Manager</li>
<li>Open the account window, by clicking the <b>Account</b> button in the top right.</li>
<li>In the account window you will be able to reset your license(s)</li></ul>
<p><br />
More information on how to reset a license can be found <a href="/index.php?title=License_reset" title="License reset"> here</a>.
<br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Development">Development</span></h1>
<p>Air Manager can be used to develop your own instruments, panels, etc.
So if you are missing an instrument in the available library, you can try building one for yourself!
</p><p>The information below will briefly explain how to get started. More information can be found on this wiki, or on our youtube channel.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Plugins">Plugins</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_New_plugin.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/f/fb/AM5_New_plugin.jpg/300px-AM5_New_plugin.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="281" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/f/fb/AM5_New_plugin.jpg/450px-AM5_New_plugin.jpg 1.5x, /images/f/fb/AM5_New_plugin.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_New_plugin.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Create new plugin</div></div></div>
<p>Air Manager can be easily extended by its plugin architecture. Active components like instruments, panel, hardware integration is all based on a plugins.
Most of these plugins are open source, and can be used to get acquainted with the matter.
</p><p>Currently there a 5 different plugins, each with its own purpose, a small introduction below.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Instrument_plugin">Instrument plugin</span></h3>
<p>An instrument plugin contains all code and assets to run an instrument.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Panel_plugin">Panel plugin</span></h3>
<p>A panel plugin is the basis of a premade panel. It lets the user add a panel without having to manually add and position all containing instruments.
The panel plugin can contain multiple layouts, which can be used to offer different layouts for different resolutions and aircraft.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Hardware_function_plugin">Hardware function plugin</span></h3>
<p>A hardware function plugin can be used to connect hardware components (LEDs, switches, buttons etc.) to the flight simulator.
The hardware function plugin is purely code based, it doesn't contain any graphical elements.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Device_plugin">Device plugin</span></h3>
<p>A device plugin can be used to connect a device (RealSimGear, Octavi, etc.) to the flight simulator.
The device plugin is purely code based, it doesn't contain any graphical elements.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Flight_Illusion_plugin">Flight Illusion plugin</span></h3>
<p>A flight illusion plugin can be used to connect Flight Illusion gauges to the flight simulator.
The flight illusion plugin is purely code based, it doesn't contain any graphical elements.
</p><p><br />
Each plugin is contained within its own folder:
</p>
<pre>\<b>info.xml</b> (contains meta data information)
\<b>logic.lua</b> (contains entry point for execution)
\<b>preview.png</b> (used by Air Manager in UI, e.g. when used is designing a panel)
\<b>lib\</b> (additional libraries)
\<b>resources\</b> (contains images, font, sounds, etc)
</pre>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Getting_started">Getting started</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Development.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/6/62/AM5_Development.jpg/300px-AM5_Development.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="266" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/6/62/AM5_Development.jpg/450px-AM5_Development.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/62/AM5_Development.jpg/600px-AM5_Development.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Development.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Development section, with instrument plugin selected</div></div></div>
<p>The best way to get your way around the code is to see what other have made.
</p>
<ul><li>Go to the development section</li>
<li>Select an instrument plugin from the left panel. The main programming script for that instrument will show at the right.</li>
<li>Start playing around, e.g.
<ul><li>Press the run button to show the instrument</li>
<li>Press the Folder button to show what the instrument plugin looks like on the file system</li>
<li>Hit the Info button to show the instrument meta data</li></ul></li></ul>
<p><br />
View the youtube video below to get you started:
<br />
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/lLvlqMBq20Y" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
<br style="clear:both;" />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Creating_a_new_plugin">Creating a new plugin</span></h2>
<p>You can create a new plugin from within Air Manager.
</p>
<ul><li>Open the Development section</li>
<li>Click on the '<b>+ Create plugin'</b> button on the top</li>
<li>Select the type of plugin you wish to create, and proceed</li>
<li>Air Manager lets you enter meta-data for your new plugin. Note that you can also change this at a later time.</li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Modifying_an_existing_plugin">Modifying an existing plugin</span></h2>
<p>Modifying an existing plugin can be as simple as selecting it and start changing its code, meta data or assets.
</p>
<div style="background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1); border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Warning.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/18px-Warning.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/27px-Warning.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/36px-Warning.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">Be wary when modifying a plugin that already exists online. If there is a new version online, Air Manager can (and will!) automatically overwrite all your hard work. It is best to clone the plugin before making adjustments</span></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Importing_a_plugin">Importing a plugin</span></h2>
<p>In the top menu click Air Manager → Import.
</p>
<h2><span id="Share_your_creation.2Fmodification_with_other_Air_Manager_users"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Share_your_creation/modification_with_other_Air_Manager_users">Share your creation/modification with other Air Manager users</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Submit.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/4/4d/AM5_Submit.jpg/300px-AM5_Submit.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="360" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/4/4d/AM5_Submit.jpg/450px-AM5_Submit.jpg 1.5x, /images/4/4d/AM5_Submit.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:AM5_Submit.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Submit a plugin to the community store</div></div></div>
<p>If you are happy with the fruits of you labour, and wish to share it with other Air Manager users, you can submit it.
</p>
<ul><li>Select your plugin in the development tab</li>
<li>Right click on the plugin, and go to 'Upload to... → Sim Innovations'</li>
<li>Fill in your name, email address and any comments</li>
<li>Check if you agree with our statement</li>
<li>We will review you submission for faults or omissions.</li>
<li>If the plugin was accepted, we will add the submitted plugins to the community store, ready to be enjoyed by other Air Manager users.</li></ul>
